title: Sujal Sarangdhar - Software Developer
summary: Sujal Sarangdhar is a Software Developer with experience in full-stack application development, machine learning, and IoT solutions. He has expertise in Python, Django, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, along with databases like MySQL and MongoDB. His project experience includes building live cab booking systems, IoT-enabled employee tracking, and machine learning classification models. He holds an MCA and BSc in Computer Science and possesses certifications in AWS Cloud Practitioner and Core Java.

responsibilities: Worked on 30+ student projects, 1 product-based project, and 1 live project using Python, Django, and machine learning.
Built and deployed full-stack applications with HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Django.
Integrated ML models and optimized backend performance.

projects.name: Vansat Cabs (Live Project)
projects.description: Developed the backend of an online cab booking system using the Django framework. Handled RESTful API integration, implemented dynamic routing with map-based location services, and managed source/destination listings. Enabled real-time route creation and trip booking functionality using geolocation data.

projects.name: IoT-Enabled Employee Tracking Software (Product Based)
projects.description: An industry-based employee attendance system using IoT for real-time tracking. The software provides live monitoring of staff in each department, ensuring accurate attendance and efficient workforce management.

projects.name: Superlative Classification Model
projects.description: A machine learning-based project consisting of three modules: image, pose, and csv. Developed using the Django Framework, it is designed to be user-friendly for individuals without prior knowledge of machine learning concepts.
